== Edit request 26 August 2025 ==

{{Edit extended-protected|answered=yes}}

'''Description of suggested change:'''

Your article states that:
"In its investigation on 20 October 2023, Forensic Architecture concluded that the blast was the result of a munition fired from the direction of Israel."

Source 21 is quoting an investigation of forensic architecture. It is clearly not quoted, but instead misquoting other newspaper articles. 
The investigation from forensic architecture states that "what happened at al-Ahli remains inconclusive".

The aim of the investigation was not to prove or disprove whether Israel or Hamas fired the attack, but to prove israeli disinformation.
The investigation just proves that the israeli disinformation about potential propellers were their own, not that they were the ones to strike the hospital, as is stated clearly in the original source.

Source:
https://forensic-architecture.org/investigation/israeli-disinformation-al-ahli-hospital


